Travis Perkins
–
Personal Trainer
NASM Certified Personal Trainer – Specializing in back strength training and corrective back
exercise.Proven track record in weight loss, strength training and sports preparation.
NASM Golf Fitness Specialist – Five years of experience with golf specific core training, golf injury
rehab and preventative training. Golf and occupational imbalance corrective training.
NASM Seniors Exercise Specialist – Post Rehab, surgery and corrective exercise training. Strength
and balance for seniors.
NASM Women’s Fitness Specialist – Strength training, weight loss and bone density with a focus
on the considerations of women’s physiological needs.
NASM Youth Fitness Specialist – Experienced training special needs youth and sport specific
preparation with consideration of youth and adolescent physiological needs.
Travis is a United States Army Veteran and a lifelong fitness enthusiast with a passion for helping
his clients achieve their goals.
Erica Cleary –
Personal Trainer
Bachelor’s Degree in Exercise Science from Arizona State University
Certified Personal Trainer
Certified Aerobics Instructor
Certified CPR/AED
Personal interests include indoor & outdoor volleyball, exercising and training & showing
her horses
Peggy Wheeler
–
Personal Trainer
NASM Certified Personal Trainer – Senior Fitness Specialist
Post Rehab, surgery and corrective exercise training. Strength and balance for seniors.
NASM Continuing Education in Corrective Exercises and Rehabilitation
Linda Serrano
–
Personal Trainer
Certified Personal Trainer with National Academy of Sports Medicine (NASM)
Certified in Senior Fitness for Anti-Aging
Certified Wellness Coach
Certified Spinning Instructor
Certified Group Fitness/Water Aerobics
Goal is to motivate clients to help strengthen themselves, especially after surgery and to help gain confidence being proud of their body.
Tonia D’Anna
–
Personal Trainer
Certified Personal Trainer for more than 10 years
Certified CPR/AED
Certified Spinning Instructor
Specializes in free weights and strength training
Personal Interest include obstacle course training and Fitness
Numerous awards for TriFitness Obstacle course competition
Married with 2 Children
Amanda Hernandez
– Personal Trainer
Certified Personal Trainer since 2016
Experienced with all fitness levels from beginner to advanced. Works with clientele ranging from high school athletes, NPC bikini competitors, clients with limited mobility and injuries, to seniors up to 90 years old.
Nutrition Specialist with the ability to develop meal plans for clients based on their goals and body type.
Her personal training programs are specifically tailored to the needs of clients. Amanda implements a variety of strength training and functional movement all while teaching proper technique, and form, as well as confidence in the gym.
Amanda specializes in strength training, body weight exercises, weight loss, flexibility, balance, and pre and post natal mothers.
John Hockley
– Personal Trainer
(ACE) Over 10 years as a Certified Personal Trainer
(CMT) Eaton Therapeutic Center
(Idea Fitness) Gravity Certification
(GMP Fitness) Back Specialist
(GMP Fitness ) Knee Specialist
(ACE) Senior Fitness Specialist
(ACE) Orthopedic Exercise Specialist
Combining his knowledge in kinesiology as a CMT and his personal training experience, he has learned how to train the body without creating damaging effects within the structures, as well as techniques to repair the structures that have been damaged due to improper lifting and ranges of motion.
Celina Stevenson
– Personal Trainer
Certified Personal Trainer with the National Academy of Sports Medicine.
Five years experience in senior fitness for balance, strength training, muscle building, and bone density.
Continuing Education Units through NASM in the neuroscience and effectiveness of aerobic training for weight loss and cardiovascular health for both one-on-one and group fitness clients.
Continuing Education Units through NASM in behavior change for better habits, TRX workouts, and cool-down techniques. Including stretching and SMR
Specialist in anti-aging exercises with a focus on face yoga, muscle strengthening for lifting, and facial vitality.
Continuing Education Units through NASM for deep core and pelvic floor restoration on pre and postpartum women of all ages.
Optimizes all workouts via teaching proper form, and breathing techniques, utilizing progressive overload, maintaining accountability for consistency, advising in proper nutrition, and engaging client mind-to-muscle connection.
Stephanie McKinley
–
Personal Trainer
Certified Exercise Therapist ~ ISSA. She can help with rehabilitation from injury or accident and other disabilities.
Certified Personal Trainer, Fitness Coach and Group Fitness ~ ISSA
Certified RYT Yoga Instructor. Slow Flow Vinyasa and Yoga Fit are some of her specialties.
Fitness Coach ~ ISSA
NDCA Professional
Stephanie is a professional ballroom and Latin dancer and former Olympic training gymnast best known for her unique exercises and sense of humor. Stephanie makes it fun!
Her focus is on functional fitness and proper technique.
She studied many styles of dance for most of her life. She competed professionally in Ballroom and Latin dance for nearly 20 years and has been teaching for 30 years.
She was a cheerleader for NFL Football and Pro Soccer teams. Stephanie competed in four seasons of Dancing with the St. Louis Stars, winning the competition twice.
Vishwa Bandara
–
Personal Trainer
NASM & ISSA Certified Personal Trainer.
Over five years training seniors and post injury rehabilitation.
Other modalities consist of weight loss, strength development, muscle imbalance correction, muscle building, agility & flexibility training, circuit training and weight strength training.
HSI Certified in CPR/AED, ACE Foundations of Strength & Conditioning.
A decade of experience training body builders and athletes specializing in Golf Fitness.
Can adapt and train all ages, body types, and fitness levels.
Originally from Sri Lanka and trained for the YMCA once I moved to the United States of America.
Susan Viola
–
Personal Trainer
Certified by the National Academy of Sports Medicine (NASM): Personal Trainer, Senior Fitness Specialist (SFS), Certified Nutrition Coach, Golf Fitness Specialist (GFS), Youth Exercise Specialist (YES), and Virtual Coaching Specialist.
Certified Precision Nutrition Coach (L1) and Oxygen Advantage Functional Breathing Instructor.
Experienced with Silver Sneakers Programs: Foundations, Classic, Circuit, Yoga, Stability, Fall Prevention, Osteoporosis and Exercise, Group Exercise and Hip Limitations, and Nutrition for Optimal Aging.
Completed NASM Continuing Education in areas including Integrated Flexibility Training, Navigating Diets, Mental Toughness, Speed and Agility, Food Labels and Portion Sizes, Weight Control Psychology, and Exercise for Anxiety Intervention.
Over 24 years of experience in health and fitness facilities, helping clients achieve their goals with expert guidance.
Utilizes the NASM Optimum Performance Training Model, progressing clients through Stabilization Endurance, Strength Endurance, Muscular Development, Maximal Strength, and Power phases.
Specializes in designing safe, time-efficient programs tailored to client goals while ensuring the process is enjoyable.
Combines advanced knowledge of fitness, nutrition, and wellness to support clients of all ages and abilities.
Passionate about helping clients build confidence, strength, and overall wellness through personalized coaching.
Paul Gianferrera
–
Racquetball Professional
USA Racquetball Association Member
Florida Racquetball Association Member
40 years of playing and instructing

Wayne Larsen, PGA
Director of Golf:
Skyview at Terra Vista & Citrus Hills Courses
Wayne was born and raised on Long Island, New York and graduated from the University of New Hampshire. Wayne enjoys every aspect of the game of golf, from teaching individuals, juniors and groups to coordinating daily events and major tournaments.  When he is not helping others with their golf games or playing, Wayne loves spending the time with his beautiful wife Cindy and precious daughter Evelyn.
Kathy Saltsman
Pro Shop Assistant
Kathy Saltsman was born and raised in Pittsburgh, PA, and moved to Crystal River in 1986, with her husband of 28 years, Philip. She has been with Citrus Hills since 2007. She is an avid golfer, who enjoys spending her time off with her husband, a senior nuclear engineer at the Crystal River nuclear plant, and her sons Philip and Tommy.
Robbie Lamparelli
Pro Shop Assistant
Robbie Lamparelli is a familiar face to the Citrus Hills Pro Shop. Robbie worked in the shop for 20 years before moving to be with her family in Buffalo, N.Y. The weather was too cold up north, so lucky for us she decided to move back! Robbie is an avid tennis player, when she’s not working or playing tennis she spends time with her husband and two children.
Stephanie Rodney
Assistant Golf Professional/Retail
Born and raised in Florida, Stephanie attended Daytona State College on a golf scholarship. She received her Bachelors in Business Management from University of South Florida. Stephanie enjoys all aspects of the golf industry, from tournaments to junior golf, but her passion is merchandising and buying for all the pro shops at Citrus Hills. Stephanie is very happy to be purchasing the newest trends and fashions for all at Citrus Hills!
Mark Panaccione
Brentwood Golf Course Pro Shop Manager
Mark and his wife Paula were born and raised in Massachusetts. They spent the majority of their adult life living in Connecticut rising their two children while Mark finished out his law enforcement career with the Connecticut State Police. He attended the University of New Haven graduating with a degree in Criminal Justice Law Enforcement Administration. He joined the Citrus Hills family in 2017, working at Skyview in many capacities, and now managing Brentwood.

Massage Therapists
Jennifer
Licensed Massage Therapist MA 50826
Specialized in Swedish Massage, Deep Tissue Massage, Sports Massage, and Craniosacral Massage Therapy
Nationally Certified Licensed Massage Therapist
Graduate of Withlacoochee Technical Institute  Inverness, FL 2007
Aeh (Kamolpan)
Born and raised in Thailand
Graduated from Withlacoochee Technical College and is certified through the Florida Board of
Massage Therapy (MA 92150)
Skilled in Swedish Massage, Deep Tissue Massage and Sports Massage.
Practices integrative massage that combines techniques to form.
Tailored session based on client needs.
Maegan
Graduated from the Florida School of Massage in Gainesville, FL, in 2001
Specializes in Swedish, hot stone, deep tissue, and neuromuscular massage
Experienced in medical massage therapy, working with acupuncturists and chiropractors
Dedicated massage therapist at BellaVita since March 2019
Cheryl
She attended the CT Center for Massage Therapy in 2012 (License #MA94478) and previously worked at Dunnellon Chiropractic as a Chiropractic Assistant and Licensed Massage Therapist (LMT)
Cheryl specializes in deep tissue massage and sports massage for pain relief, improved flexibility, and faster muscle recovery
She creates integrated, customized treatment plans tailored to each client’s individual needs and goals
Cheryl is certified in advanced modalities including lymphatic drainage, myofascial release, trigger point therapy, and neuromuscular massage therapy
She is committed to promoting overall wellness and helping clients achieve optimal physical health
Olivia
Graduated from Withlacoochee Technical College in 2016
Licensed through the Fl Board of Massage Therapy MA8607
200+ hours of training in Medical Massage and treatment protocols
Specializing in Swedish, Deep Tissue, Reflexology and Sports Massage
She utilizes her expertise in various techniques to promote relaxation, reduce pain and improve the clients overall well-being
Customized treatments based on each client’s physical conditions and needs
Nail Technicians
Jen (Xian)
Jen is originally from China, and has lived in Shanghai and Shenzhen
Specializes in manicures, pedicures, with different shapes of acrylic nails, oval, coffin, square, stiletto, almond with full set and fill in, white tip, pink and white, and dipping powder nails (with tip or no tip)
Has an eye for detail and can do nail designs as well
Bobbie
Licensed Nail Technician
Specializing in Manicure’s and Pedicure’s with relaxing Massage techniques as well as nail acrylic and gel enhancements
Licensed Esthetician
Specializes in Nail Art – Freehand Intricate Designs and Abstract Art
Shelly Ann
Licensed by the state of Florida and graduate of Margate School of Beauty since 1982 (License # FV9600753)
Specializes in manicures, pedicures, acrylics, gels on both natural nails and nail tips
Has an eye for detail, creativity and the ability to comply with safety and health guidelines
Lisa
Full Specialist License # FS862909
Licensed Nail Technician Since 2003
Licensed Esthetician Since 2004
Specialties Include: Acrylic, Gel, Overlays, Sculptured, Shellac, Manicures, Pedicures, Facials and Waxing
Education: WTI & Ocala Putting on Tips
Michelle G.
Michelle has been a Nail Tech Specialist since 2007.
She specializes in natural nail care, acrylic overlay or with enhancements and is shellac certified.
All or her nail art is all done by hand. She is extremely detailed-oriented and loves encapsulating enhancements and all kinds of funky/ abstract nails.
She is the ingrown toe Nail guru, specializing in ingrown toe nail removal even extreme ingrown toe nail removal.
She specializes in pedicures with a relaxing massage technique to rejuvenate your feet and make them feel like new again.
Ashton
Ashton has been a Licensed Nail Technician since 2007
She specializes in powder dips, gel enhancements and natural nail care.
Ashton is committed to ensuring each individual receives the best care
Mariely
Mariely is originally from Bayamón, Puerto Rico
She graduated from Metropolitan Technical College (2004) with a technical degree in aesthetics, body waxing, and makeup
Earned Full Specialist license from Beyond Institute at Career Center (2017)
She specializes in skin care, hand and foot care, body waxing, and makeup
Michelle D.
With over 20 years of experience in both nail and skincare, Michelle is committed to providing consistent, pleasant, and relaxing service at every visit.
She offers a full range of nail care services, including manicures, pedicures, gel polish, and Plexigel by CND enhancements for broken or damaged nails.
Michelle is also skilled in specialty nail care, providing gentle relief for ingrown nails and smoothing thickened nails for added comfort.
She takes great pride in offering personalized care and values each guest’s time and preferences.
Not Pictured: Renee
Estheticians / Skin Care
Carina
Graduated from Florida, Carina has a great understanding of customer service and the hospitality industry. Her clients benefit from her hands-on treatment experience with a natural approach.
Specializing in Customized Facials, Chemical Peels, MicroNeedling, Microdermabrasion, LED Lights Therapy, Skin Scrubber, Micro Current, High Frequency, Ultrasonic, Paraffin Wax Facials, Galvanic Treatments, Back Facials, Body Skin Treatments and Lash Lift and Tints.
Bobbie
With over 10 years of experience, Bobbie is passionate about helping clients achieve their best skin through personalized treatments and expert skincare routines.
Licensed esthetician dedicated to helping clients achieve their best skin through personalized treatments and skincare routines
Bobbie has expertise in customized facials, Dermaplaning, Microdermabrasion Hydrodermabrasion and Chemical Peels
Bobbie focuses on both skin health and appearance, her personalized approach ensures each client leaves feeling refreshed, confident, and glowing
Denise Chandler APRN, FNP-C, PMHNP-BC – Botox and Dermal Fillers
Denise graduated from Lake-Sumter State College with an Associate of Science in nursing and an Associate of Arts degree.
She went to the University of Central Florida for a Bachelor of Science in nursing
She obtained her first master’s degree from the University of Phoenix in nursing with a specialty in nursing/healthcare education
Her second master’s degree is from the University of Cincinnati as a family nurse practitioner with her certification from the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners
She also has training in Aesthetics from Empire Medical, X-Medica, Palette Resources, Aesthetic Immersion, and Hans Biomed
She has her own practice in Bushnell, FL, providing minimally invasive Botox and filler procedures, women’s health services, mental health, DOT physicals, and weight loss
Rola El Halabi – Permanent Makeup
Clinician
With extensive training in permanent makeup and cosmetic enhancement, she is committed to delivering exceptional results that will exceed your expectations.
As the founder of Rola Permanent Cosmetics, she specializes in enhancing natural beauty through precision and artistic skill.
Through a consultative approach, she works closely with you to understand your unique needs and aesthetic goals.
Specializing in
Ombre Powder Eyebrows, Nano Brows, Eyeliner, Lip Blush, Scalp MicroP (SMP),
Scar Camouflage
, and more.
Permanent makeup enhances your natural features, boosts confidence, provides a polished, natural look every day, saving time and money.
